# 🧠 Market-QWAN

### Institutional Quantitative Platform for Adaptive Neural Forecasting & Systemic Risk Modeling

Mini-API / Frontend Repository:
[https://github.com/goldenluke/market-qwan](https://github.com/goldenluke/market-qwan)

---

## 📌 Overview

**Market-QWAN** is an experimental quantitative research platform designed for:

* Portfolio-level neural time series forecasting
* Regime-aware financial modeling
* Systemic risk monitoring
* Interactive institutional dashboards
* Modular training and inference workflows

The system integrates machine learning, econophysics-inspired systemic diagnostics, and modern software architecture to provide a robust research-grade quantitative infrastructure.

The platform is built with strict architectural separation between:

* Model training
* Inference
* Visualization
* API layer

This separation ensures runtime stability, modularity, and scalability.

---

# 🚀 Core Capabilities

## 🔮 Neural Forecasting Engine

Market-QWAN uses **NHITS (Neural Hierarchical Interpolation for Time Series)** via NeuralForecast to produce portfolio-level forecasts.

Features:

* Multi-asset forecasting
* Configurable:

  * Tickers
  * Input window (context size)
  * Forecast horizon
* Model persistence (`.pkl`)
* Reproducible training via CLI or API
* Expected return estimation at portfolio level

Designed for research-grade adaptive forecasting workflows.

---

## 🧠 Regime-Aware Modeling (Planned Expansion)

* Hidden Markov Models (HMM)
* State-dependent return dynamics
* Regime probability inference
* Transition matrix diagnostics
* Future regime-conditioned forecasting

This extends forecasting beyond static time series assumptions.

---

## 🌐 Systemic Risk Monitoring

The platform includes systemic diagnostics inspired by network theory and econophysics:

* Largest eigenvalue stress (λ_max)
* Correlation heatmap visualization
* Rolling susceptibility proxy
* Network density
* Stress index aggregation
* Dynamic correlation monitoring

These tools allow monitoring of structural market fragility.

---

## 📊 Institutional Dashboard (Streamlit)

The Streamlit dashboard provides:

* Forecast visualization
* Historical performance plots
* Model selection dropdown
* Correlation network display
* Clean separation from training engine

It is designed strictly for inference and visualization to avoid training instability.

---

## 🌐 External Training Interface (Flask)

A dedicated Flask-based training server enables:

* Asynchronous training
* TailwindCSS-powered frontend
* Dynamic model listing
* Parameter configuration UI
* Safe model serialization
* Background training execution

This prevents:

* Streamlit crashes during heavy training
* Torch subprocess conflicts
* Runtime instability
* Mixed inference-training sessions

---

# 🏗 System Architecture

The system follows a layered architecture:

Streamlit (Visualization Only)
↓
Flask Training Server
↓
CLI Training Script (`train_forecast.py`)
↓
Saved Models (`models/*.pkl`)

This modular architecture ensures:

* Decoupled responsibilities
* Stable UI operation
* Clean model lifecycle management
* Easier scaling to production environments

---

# 📂 Project Structure

```
market-qwan/
│
├── dashboard.py              # Streamlit dashboard
├── trainer_server.py         # Flask API + Trainer UI
├── train_forecast.py         # CLI training script
├── models/                   # Saved trained models (.pkl)
├── templates/
│   └── trainer.html          # Tailwind trainer interface
├── src/
│   ├── qwan_forecast_model.py
│   ├── qwan_regime_model.py
│   ├── qwan_systemic_risk.py
│   └── ...
├── requirements.txt
└── README.md
```

---

# ⚙️ Installation

## 1️⃣ Clone Repository

```bash
git clone https://github.com/goldenluke/market-qwan.git
cd market-qwan
```

---

## 2️⃣ Create Virtual Environment

(Recommended: Python 3.12)

```bash
python -m venv market-qwan-env
source market-qwan-env/bin/activate
```

---

## 3️⃣ Install Dependencies

```bash
pip install --upgrade pip
pip install torch neuralforecast streamlit flask flask-cors numpy pandas plotly scikit-learn networkx hmmlearn statsmodels yfinance
```

---

# 🚀 Running the System

## 🧠 Start Training Server

```bash
python trainer_server.py
```

Open:

[http://127.0.0.1:5050](http://127.0.0.1:5050)

---

## 📊 Start Streamlit Dashboard

```bash
streamlit run dashboard.py
```

---

# 🔮 CLI Training (Optional Advanced Mode)

```bash
python train_forecast.py \
  --tickers AAPL,MSFT \
  --input_size 60 \
  --horizon 10 \
  --model_name model_test
```

Models are saved in:

```
models/model_test.pkl
```

